<HEADLINE>
<P>
MORNING REPORT: POP/ROCK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By GREG BRAXTON , Arts and entertainment reports from The Times, national and 
international news services and the nation's press. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
'Wall' of Sound: Sinead O'Connor, Van Morrison and Joni Mitchell will be among 
the artists participating in the performance of former Pink Floyd leader Roger 
Waters' "The Wall" at the Berlin Wall July 21. 
</P>
<P>
The show will be staged on Potsdamerplatz in the shadow of the Brandenburg Gate 
between East and West Berlin. Other performers playing roles include Cyndi 
Lauper, Jerry Hall, Marianne Faithfull, Bryan Adams, Thomas Dolby, the Band, 
Albert Finney and Tim Curry. Waters has been rehearsing the score with the 
all-star Bleeding Heart Band for two months. GREG BRAXTON 
</P>
</TEXT>
<GRAPHIC>
<P>
Photo, Waters 
</P>
</GRAPHIC>
